  "prompt_text": "Prove that the square root of 2 is irrational.",
  "response_text": "To prove that the square root of 2 is irrational, we will use the method of contradiction. We assume that the square root of 2 is rational and then show that this assumption leads to a contradiction.\n\nAssume that the square root of 2 is rational, which means it can be expressed as a fraction in the form of a/b, where a and b are integers with no common factors other than 1 (i.e., a and b are coprime), and b is not equal to zero.\n\nSquaring both sides of the equation, we get:\n\na\u00b2 = 2b\u00b2\n\nNow, let's multiply both sides by 2 to get rid of the left side having an even number of terms:\n\n2a\u00b2 = 2 * 2b\u00b2\n\nSimplifying the equation, we get:\n\n2a\u00b2 = 4b\u00b2\n\nDividing both sides by 2, we have:\n\na\u00b2 = 2b\u00b2\n\nComparing this equation with the original assumption, we see that they are identical. However, this means that a\u00b2 is equal to b\u00b2 (since we assumed that a\u00b2 = 2b\u00b2), which implies that a and b are perfect squares.\n\nSince a and b are coprime, we can write a as a product of prime numbers (a = p\u2081\u2071 * p\u2082\u2071\u2080, where p\u2081 and p\u2082 are distinct prime numbers), and b as a product of another set of prime numbers (b = q\u2081\u2071 * q\u2082\u2071\u2080, where q\u2081 and q\u2082 are distinct prime numbers).\n\nNow, we can write a\u00b2 as:\n\na\u00b2 = (p\u2081\u2071 * p\u2082\u2071\u2080)\u00b2 = p\u2081\u00b2\u2071 * p\u2082\u00b2\u2071\u2080\n\nSimilarly, we can write b\u00b2 as:\n\nb\u00b2 = (q\u2081\u2071 * q\u2082\u2071\u2080)\u00b2 = q\u2081\u00b2\u2071 * q\u2082\u00b2\u2071\u2080\n\nSince a\u00b2 = 2b\u00b2, we have:\n\np\u2081\u00b2\u2071 * p\u2082\u00b2\u2071\u2080 = 2 * q\u2081\u00b2\u2071 * q\u2082\u00b2\u2071\u2080\n\nNow, we can see that if p\u2081\u00b2\u2071 and q\u2081\u00b2\u2071 are both even, then p\u2082\u00b2\u2071 * q\u2082\u00b2\u2071\u2080 must be even, which contradicts the fact that the product of two odd numbers (p\u2082\u00b2\u2071 * q\u2082\u00b2\u2071\u2080) cannot be equal to 2",
